last_episode_to_air.name: Grand Finale Variety Extravaganza: Part 2
last_episode_to_air.overview: It's the crowning moment of the two-part Grand Finale, and all the Queens hit the stage for an unforgettable Variety Extravaganza! Three badges are up for grabs, and a new voting twist could change everything! In the end, only one queen can win.

name: RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars
overview: The most celebrated competitors from RuPaul's Drag Race vie for a second chance to enter Drag Race herstory. This drag queen showdown is filled with plenty of heated competition, lip-syncing for the legacy, and, of course, the All-Stars Snatch Game.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: RuPaul welcomes back the best of the best, the top queens from Drag Race seasons 1-4, and they're ready to lip-synch for their lives to determine which of these all-stars will claim the ultimate title and be declared Queen amongst queens.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: A twist on the mega-hit RuPaul's Drag Race as queens from previous seasons are pitted against each other in a wig-to-wig drag battle royale.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: All Stars compete for $100,000 and a chance to be inducted into RuPaul's Drag Race Hall of Fame.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: Unforgettable queens and Drag Race royalty take another shot at capturing the crown on RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars. The competitions will be as fierce as the runways, but only one queen can cement her legacy in The Drag Race Hall of Fame.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: Drag Race royalty Alexis Mateo, Blair St. Clair, Derrick Barry, India Ferrah, Jujubee, Mariah Paris Balenciaga, Mayhem Miller, Miz Cracker, Ongina and Shea Coulee sashay back onto the runway for a chance at snatching the All Stars crown and nabbing a spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: Thirteen legendary queens return to RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars to claim a spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame! With more gag-worthy talents, jaw-dropping looks and epic performances, this is the biggest season of All Stars ever!

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: For the first time ever in the herstory of RuPaul's Drag Race, the series will feature a cast of all former winners returning to compete for the title "Queen of All Queens" and a cash prize of $200,000.

seasons.name: Season 8
seasons.overview: RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars brings back 12 of your favorite queens from across the Ru-niverse to compete for a coveted spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame! Plus, a new "Fame Games" twist means there's more than one way to win!

seasons.name: Season 9
seasons.overview: Who will save the world? Drag Queens! RuPaul brings together eight of her most powerful All Stars to slay it forward in the name of charity. All season long, the queens will battle as they raise thousands of dollars for their favorite causes. But in the end, only one will win a coveted spot in the prestigious Drag Race Hall of Fame.

episodes.name: It Takes Two
episodes.overview: Twelve All Stars arrive to compete for $100,000 and a chance to become the first inductee into RuPaul’s Drag Race Hall of Fame.

episodes.name: RuPaul's Gaff-In
episodes.overview: The queens find themselves battling for laughs while impersonating their favorite celebrities on “RuPaul’s Gaff-In” with Vicki Lawrence’s “Mama”.

episodes.name: Queens Behaving Badly
episodes.overview: The queens hit the streets of Hollywood to prank unsuspecting passers-by.

episodes.name: All Star Girl Groups
episodes.overview: Legendary children Kady Z, Jillian Hervey and Kelly Osbourne join the queens to form All Star girl groups in a battle of the divas for the fiercest set.

episodes.name: Dynamic Drag Duos
episodes.overview: The final four assume super hero and super foe alter egos and go to epic heights to vanquish their nemesis.

episodes.name: The Grand Finale
episodes.overview: For the final challenge, RuPaul sends her All Stars on a junket that culminates with a stand-up routine at L.A.’s Comedy Store.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: RuPaul welcomes back the best of the best, the top queens from Drag Race seasons 1-4, and they're ready to lip-synch for their lives to determine which of these all-stars will claim the ultimate title and be declared Queen amongst queens.

episodes.name: All Star Talent Show Extravaganza
episodes.overview: Ten Queens return to compete for $100,000 and a place in the Drag Race Hall of Fame. The first test is to compete in a drag talent show. With guest judge Raven-Symoné.

episodes.name: All Stars Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens impersonate celebrities in a quick-witted TV game show and burn rubber in a latex runway. With guest judge Ross Mathews.

episodes.name: HERstory Of The World
episodes.overview: The queens are challenged to perform in a lip-syncing dance number inspired by the legendary historical women. Fashion designer Jeremy Scott guest judges.

episodes.name: Drag Movie Shequels
episodes.overview: The queens acting chops are tested in parody movie sequels of RuPaul's favorite movies. Pussycat Doll Nicole Scherzinger guest judges.

episodes.name: Revenge Of The Queens
episodes.overview: The queens must perform a live stand-up comedy act in front of an audience of judgmental drag queens. Ross Mathews returns to guest judge.

episodes.name: Drag Fish Tank
episodes.overview: The queens design and market drag-influenced products. Entrepreneur Marcus Lemonis (CNBC's The Profit) co-stars, and comedian Graham Norton guest judges.

episodes.name: Family That Drags Together
episodes.overview: The queens makeover family members; actress Aubrey Plaza judges

episodes.name: All Stars Supergroup
episodes.overview: The queens must write original rap lyrics and perform as a girl group; crowning a winner.

episodes.name: Reunion
episodes.overview: The All Star queens reunite to dish about the most shocking, glamorous and sickening moments of the season. Hosted by the Emmy Award winning RuPaul.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: A twist on the mega-hit RuPaul's Drag Race as queens from previous seasons are pitted against each other in a wig-to-wig drag battle royale.

episodes.name: All-Star Variety Show
episodes.overview: A mystery 10th queen joins the nine All Stars competing for $100,000 and a place in the Drag Race Hall of Fame. The first test is to compete in a drag variety show.

episodes.name: Divas Lip Sync Live
episodes.overview: The queens go full diva in a lip-syncing dance number inspired by the classic TV specials "VH1 Divas Live". With guest judge Vanessa Williams and choreographer Todrick Hall.

episodes.name: The B*tchelor
episodes.overview: The queens' improvisation skills are tested in an unscripted dating show. Constance Zimmer and Jeffrey Bowyer-Chapman guest judge.

episodes.name: All Stars Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens impersonate celebrities in a quick-witted TV game show. Fashion designer Marc Jacobs stops by the workroom, while Kristin Chenoweth and Nicole Byer (Girl Code) guest judge.

episodes.name: Pop Art Ball
episodes.overview: The queens design wearable soup cans inspired by Andy Warhol, and create Studio 54 disco looks. Tituss Burgess and Shay Mitchell guest judge.

episodes.name: Handmaids To Kitty Girls
episodes.overview: The eliminated queens return to the competition for revenge. But first the queens must audition for RuPaul's new girl group, the Kitty Girls. Spice Girl Emma Bunton ("Baby Spice") and Adam Lambert guest judge.

episodes.name: My Best Squirrelfriend's Dragsmaids Wedding Trip
episodes.overview: The queens’ acting chops are tested in a girl comedy blockbuster scene. Democratic Leader Nancy Pelosi stops by the workroom, while Chris Colfer and Garcelle Beauvais guest judge.

episodes.name: A Jury Of Their Queers
episodes.overview: The queens must write and perform a rap on RuPaul’s new hit single and conquer a one-take choreography performance. But before a winner can be crowned, RuPaul invites the eliminated queens to weigh in.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: All Stars compete for $100,000 and a chance to be inducted into RuPaul's Drag Race Hall of Fame.

episodes.name: All Star Super Queen Variety Show
episodes.overview: The Queens' first challenge is a salute to LGBTQ troops in an All Star-Spangled Variety Show; extra special guest judge Jenifer Lewis joins.

episodes.name: Super Girl Groups, Henny
episodes.overview: RuPaul's Drag Race Season 3 contestant Stacy Layne Matthews returns for a musical collaboration with the queens of All Stars Season 4.

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: The queens try out their best celebrity impressions for a romantic take on Snatch Game, and guest judges Gus Kenworthy and Keiynan Lonsdale weigh in on the competition.

episodes.name: Jersey Justice
episodes.overview: The All Stars get into character as litigants on an unscripted courtroom parody with New Jersey Justice Michelle Visage, and Zoe Kravitz and Erica Ash sit in as guest judges.

episodes.name: Roast In Peace
episodes.overview: The All Stars put their stand-up comedy chops to the test in a eulogy-style Roast of Lady Bunny, and Cecily Strong and Yvette Nicole Brown guest-judge the competition.

episodes.name: LaLaPaRuZa
episodes.overview: The All Stars are in for a surprise when they discover that the eliminated queens have returned for a lip sync smackdown and the opportunity to re-enter the competition.

episodes.name: Queens Of Clubs
episodes.overview: The All Stars design their own nightclubs (complete with entertainment and VIP experiences), and Rita Ora and New York City nightlife promoter Susanne Bartsch guest judge.

episodes.name: RuPaul's Best Judy's Race
episodes.overview: The All Stars give their best friends drag queen makeovers and perform a Judy Garland tribute, and Frances Bean Cobain and Ellen Pompeo sit in on the judges' panel.

episodes.name: Sex And The Kitty, Girl 3
episodes.overview: The All Stars put their acting skills to the test in a "Sex and the City"-inspired mockumentary, and Felicity Huffman and Jason Wu sit in on the judges' panel.

episodes.name: Super Queen Grand Finale
episodes.overview: In the final challenge of the season, the remaining girls write superhero-inspired lyrics and perform original choreography for RuPaul's "Super Queen".

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: Unforgettable queens and Drag Race royalty take another shot at capturing the crown on RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars. The competitions will be as fierce as the runways, but only one queen can cement her legacy in The Drag Race Hall of Fame.

episodes.name: All Star Variety Extravaganza
episodes.overview: The Season 5 All Stars make their werkroom entrances, extra special guest judge Ricky Martin gives a lesson in bilingual shade, and a new elimination twist is Ruvealed.

episodes.name: I’m In Love!
episodes.overview: The All Stars perform girl-group songs about their celebrity crushes and strut the runway in Love the Skin You're In lewks, and Tessa Thompson and Madison Beer guest judge.

episodes.name: Get A Room!
episodes.overview: The All Stars design their own boutique hotel suite experiences and show off three-in-one lewks on the runway, and Nicole Byer and Martyn Lawrence Bullard guest judge.

episodes.name: SheMZ
episodes.overview: The All Stars improv their way through celebrity scandals on a TMZ-inspired tabloid reality series and then walk the runway in camo couture, and Sarah Hyland guest judges.

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: Guest judges Tommy Dorfman and Jeffrey Bowyer-Chapman join the All Stars for a dating-themed version of Snatch Game, and the category on the runway is Prom Queen Fantasy.

episodes.name: The Charles Family Backyard Ball
episodes.overview: For the barbecue-themed Charles Family Backyard Ball, the All Stars design runway lewks using materials that can be found in a yard, and Bebe Rexha guest judges.

episodes.name: Stand-Up Smackdown
episodes.overview: The All Stars perform stand-up sets for guest judges Sam Richardson and Jane Krakowski at RuPaul's Shady Shack, and the category on the runway is Freak Out.

episodes.name: Clap Back!
episodes.overview: Before the next All Star is inducted into the Drag Race Hall of Fame, the eliminated queens return, and the Top Three girls write and perform verses of RuPaul's "Clap Back!".

5.name: Season 5
5.overview: Drag Race royalty Alexis Mateo, Blair St. Clair, Derrick Barry, India Ferrah, Jujubee, Mariah Paris Balenciaga, Mayhem Miller, Miz Cracker, Ongina and Shea Coulee sashay back onto the runway for a chance at snatching the All Stars crown and nabbing a spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame.

episodes.name: All Star Variety Extravaganza
episodes.overview: The Queens of All Stars 6 are back to compete for a spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame. To kick off the competition, the dolls showcase their best talents on the Main Stage. Plus, the iconic Miss Piggy pops by to prove that reading IS fundamental.

episodes.name: The Blue Ball
episodes.overview: The All Stars storm the runway in their bold and blue-tiful best - in the Blue Ball! Guest Judge Big Freedia helps decide whose design will earn a blue ribbon.

episodes.name: Side Hustles
episodes.overview: Even the best queen needs a side hustle, so the All Stars must create commercials to sell their services. Tia Mowry joins as guest judge.

episodes.name: Halftime Headliners
episodes.overview: Fireworks fly as the All Stars celebrate and impersonate their favorite divas in an epic halftime show. Jamal Sims whips the dolls into shape as guest choreographer and judge.

episodes.name: Pink Table Talk
episodes.overview: The All Stars serve up piping hot tea as hosts of an up close and personal talk show, Pink Table Talk. Guest Judge Aisha Tyler stops by to join the kiki.

episodes.name: Ru-Merican Horror Story: Coven Girl
episodes.overview: Who is the baddest witch of all? Find out as the All Stars showcase their acting chops in this spooky spoof. Superstar Angela Bassett offers bewitching advice, and Guest Judge Emma Roberts stops by to cast a spell of her own.

episodes.name: Show Up Queen
episodes.overview: Drag and activism come together as the All Stars record and perform an inspiring anthem: "Show Up Queen!" Designer extraordinaire Zaldy brings his eye for fashion to the judging panel.

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: The All Stars serve up their best celebrity impressions in a dating show version of the Snatch Game. Who's getting lucky? Guest judges Fortune Feimster and Cheyenne Jackson search for their perfect snatch match; superstar designer Ms. Tina Knowles- Lawson joins on the mainstage.

episodes.name: Drag Tots
episodes.overview: The All Stars turn themselves into magical characters fit for the hit animated series, Drag Tots. Guest Judge Charli XCX stops by for this fierce foray into fantasy and fun.

episodes.name: Rudemption Lip-Sync Smackdown
episodes.overview: The eliminated queens are back to compete in an epic Lip Sync Smackdown and a chance to return to the competition.

episodes.name: The Charisma, Uniqueness, Nerve and Talent Monologues
episodes.overview: The All Stars take the stage to share hilarious and heartwarming true stories in a performance challenge that decides who makes it to the Grand Finale! Actors Jermaine Fowler and Alec Mapa coach the queens; writer/director Justin Simien joins the judges’ panel.

episodes.name: This Is Our Country
episodes.overview: Who will take home the crown? A spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame is at stake as the finalists write, record, and perform verses to RuPaul's new song This is Our Country, featuring country music legend Tanya Tucker.

6.name: Season 6
6.overview: Thirteen legendary queens return to RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars to claim a spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame! With more gag-worthy talents, jaw-dropping looks and epic performances, this is the biggest season of All Stars ever!

episodes.name: Legends
episodes.overview: Eight legendary RuPaul's Drag Race winners have returned to battle for the title of "Queen of All Queens." After a raucous reading challenge and an epic runway session with supermodel Naomi Campbell, our queens must put together a show-stopping performance of RuPaul's song "Legends." Special Guest Judge Cameron Diaz brings her star power to the Drag Race panel.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: For the first time in Drag Race herstory, the crowned queens must perform two iconic celebrity impersonations in a Snatch Game Double-Header! International style icon Daphne Guiness joins the judges' panel.

episodes.name: The Realness of Fortune Ball
episodes.overview: The legendary queens put their spin on the classic Drag Race ball challenge, serving 3 looks each in the "Realness of Fortune" Ball. Vanna White is in the house to make sure things are letter-perfect, and actress Kirby Howell-Baptiste graces the judges' panel.

episodes.name: Fairytale Justice
episodes.overview: All rise! The legends are telling tall tales in court as they bring their best storybook characters to the witness stand in this twisted improv challenge. Drag Race veteran Jeffrey Bowyer-Chapman is back to testify on the judges' panel.

episodes.name: Draguation Speeches
episodes.overview: The queens deliver inspiring and irreverent commencement speeches for draguates around the world. Nikki Glaser shares her comedic expertise and helps Mama Ru pick this week's Valedictorian.

episodes.name: Total Ru-quest Live
episodes.overview: The queens live out their Y2K girl group fantasies on a dragtastic tribute to TRL! And on the runway, category is: Night of 1,000 Dolly Partons. Pop star Tove Lo joins the judges' panel.

episodes.name: Legendary Legend Looks
episodes.overview: Fashion Icon and Supermodel of the World, Rupaul, challenges the crowned queens to use their divine design skills to transform eight of her legendary looks. Iconic and effervescent designer Betsey Johnson spices up the judges' panel.

episodes.name: Santa's School for Girls
episodes.overview: Ho ho ho! The queens make the yuletide gayer as they star in the twisted new holiday cult classic, "Santa's School for Girls." Acclaimed film director Janicza Bravo brings her expertise to set, and reviews the queens' performances on the judges panel.

episodes.name: Dance Like a Drag Queen
episodes.overview: The queens try to break the internet by creating an original dance video challenge. On the runway, category is: What Lies Beneath. Ben Platt lends his voice to the judges' panel.

episodes.name: The Kennedy Davenport Center Honors Hall of Shade
episodes.overview: The queens take the stage to roast each other at the first-ever Kennedy Davenport Center "Hall of Shade" Honors. Pulitzer prize-winning journalist, Ronan Farrow, joins the esteemed judges' panel.

episodes.name: Drag Race Gives Back Variety Extravaganza
episodes.overview: The crowned queens give 'til it hurts, as they star in a charity talent show extravaganza! But first, they each join RuPaul and Michelle Visage for an intimate tic-tac chit-chat! Super-hot actress and comedian Hannah Einbinder joins the judges' panel.

episodes.name: Lip Sync LaLaPaRuza
episodes.overview: It's a lip sync battle royale, as the crowned queens take the stage for the most epic Lip Sync LalaPaRuza in Drag Race herstory. And in the end, one legend will be crowned Queen of All Queens.

7.name: Season 7
7.overview: For the first time ever in the herstory of RuPaul's Drag Race, the series will feature a cast of all former winners returning to compete for the title "Queen of All Queens" and a cash prize of $200,000.

episodes.name: The Fame Games
episodes.overview: Twelve Drag Race All Stars return for a second chance at the crown and a cash prize of $200,000. And this season, there are two ways to win! After a sickening fashion show mini-challenge, the queens thrill iconic guest judge Idina Menzel.

episodes.name: It's RDR Live!
episodes.overview: “Live from Tuckahoe... it’s RDR Live!” The All Stars are challenged to serve up laughs in a hilarious Drag Race send-up of the iconic sketch comedy show. SNL alum Bobby Moynihan and special guest judge Robin Thede lend their comedic expertise.

episodes.name: The Supermarket Ball
episodes.overview: The All Stars storm the runway – and the grocery aisle – transforming everyday supermarket items into supermodel-worthy fashions! Guest judge Jojo Siwa is having a ball as she checks out the parade of 30 gagworthy garments.

episodes.name: Screen Queens
episodes.overview: The Golden Age of Television gets even sparklier, as the All Stars create and star in their own sickening scripted TV series trailers, directed by Emmy® Award winner Michelle Visage. Euphoria actress Maude Apatow helps decide which trailer is “must-she TV.”

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: Love is in the air as the queens serve up their flirtiest celebrity impersonations for guest judges Bowen Yang and Matt Rogers in the romantic and raucous “Snatch Game of Love.” But, before the queens hit the runway, the Werkroom is rocked by a game-changing shocker.

episodes.name: JOAN: The Unauthorized Rusical
episodes.overview: The All Stars channel Hollywood royalty, singing and dancing in “JOAN: The Unauthorized Rusical,” celebrating “Mommie Dearest” herself, Joan Crawford! Then, from one legend to another... On the Runway, category is “Night of 1,000 Grace Joneses.” Choreographer and director Adam Shankman coaches the queens and joins the judges’ panel.

episodes.name: Forensic Queens
episodes.overview: The Queens’ improv talents are on full display, as they star in a twisted true-crime show, examining the mystery, “Wha-Ha-Happened to Lil’ Poundcake.”

episodes.name: You're a Winner Baby!
episodes.overview: RuPaul challenges the queens to create looks worthy of the Drag Race Hall of Fame, inspired by past All Stars champions. Drag Race legends Raven and Shannel bring some style guidance to the workroom.

episodes.name: Carson Kressley, This is Your Gay Life
episodes.overview: The All Stars heat things up to roast beloved judge Carson Kressley in front of a live audience, including a very extra-special surprise guest queen & judge! Michelle Visage and comedian Alec Mapa coach the queens.

episodes.name: The Letter "L"
episodes.overview: Celebrating the L in LGBTQIA+ , the queens share the miracle of drag with new lesbian sisters, transforming the fabulous queer women into fabulous drag queens.

episodes.name: The Fame Games Variety Extravaganza
episodes.overview: They’re back! The eliminated queens return to the workroom and read each other to filth before showing off their charisma, uniqueness, nerve and talent one last time in the Fame Games Variety Extravaganza. Comedian Ego Nwodim joins the judges’ panel.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The time has come… to crown two queens! First, Ru will announce who fans voted “Queen of the Fame Games!” Then, our finalists will battle for a spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame!

8.name: Season 8
8.overview: RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars brings back 12 of your favorite queens from across the Ru-niverse to compete for a coveted spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame! Plus, a new "Fame Games" twist means there's more than one way to win!

episodes.name: Drag Queens Save The World
episodes.overview: Eight All Stars return to compete to win $200,000 for their favorite charity, and a spot in the Drag Race Hall of Fame. They serve up an epic performance of the anthem "Drag Queens Save the World," and Keke Palmer joins for this gagworthy premiere.

episodes.name: The Paint Ball
episodes.overview: The Queens present a total of 24 iconic looks on the runway - including hand-painted masterpieces created in the Werk Room - in the art-inspired Paint Ball. Oscar-nominated actor Stephanie Hsu joins the judges' panel to appraise the Queens' work.

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: Romance is in the air as the Queens impersonate celebrities in the Snatch Game of Love. But when two All Stars want to play the same celeb, things get spicy! Meanwhile, a twist means that more badges are up for grabs! Pop superstar Anitta stops by.

episodes.name: Smokin' Hot Firefighter Makeover
episodes.overview: This week begins with fiery accusations, and when the Queens are tasked with transforming four sexy firefighters into hot pop stars, things really start to sizzle! Country music duo the Brothers Osborne join the judges panel and feel the heat.

episodes.name: Property Queens
episodes.overview: This week our All Stars' put their sales skills to the test, as they create raucous real estate commercials for some preposterous properties. Superstar Realtor Tracy Tutor and Comedian Alec Mapa stop by to assess what's on the market.

episodes.name: The National Drag Convention Roast
episodes.overview: While the ruby snippers cause icy vibes in the workroom, it’s hotter than an oven on the main stage, as the queens roast each other to a crisp. Television icon Ruta Lee joins the panel to witness the hilarious jabs.

episodes.name: Meeting In The Ladies Room
episodes.overview: This week, the All-Stars get slap happy as they costar with RuPaul in an acting challenge inspired by some of cinema’s most classic catfights. Foxy actor Colton Haynes joins the judging panel to take in all the drama!

episodes.name: Make Your Own Kind Of Rusic
episodes.overview: After hard feelings rock the workroom, Mama Ru challenges the dolls to create chart-topping looks inspired by her hit songs. Fashion icon Jeremy Scott joins the judge panel to decide which looks are bops and which are flops!

episodes.name: Rosemarie's Baby Shower: The Rusical
episodes.overview: This week, the All Stars dance with the devil in a spooky-ooky Rusical that leaves the judges shook! Dance music legend Kristine W joins the panel for a twisted good time.

episodes.name: Lip Sync LaLaPaRuza Smackdown
episodes.overview: The competition is closer than ever, so when Ru announces that the Queens must Lip Sync for their badges this week, the All Stars go into Assassin mode to slay the stage! Who will be the last Queen standing?

episodes.name: Grand Finale Variety Extravaganza: Part 1
episodes.overview: This week, Mama Ru drops a gag-worthy twist on the All-Stars... Before their final challenge of the season, the queens must cast a game-changing vote - and it's anybody’s crown to win!

episodes.name: Grand Finale Variety Extravaganza: Part 2
episodes.overview: It's the crowning moment of the two-part Grand Finale, and all the Queens hit the stage for an unforgettable Variety Extravaganza! Three badges are up for grabs, and a new voting twist could change everything! In the end, only one queen can win.

9.name: Season 9
9.overview: Who will save the world? Drag Queens! RuPaul brings together eight of her most powerful All Stars to slay it forward in the name of charity. All season long, the queens will battle as they raise thousands of dollars for their favorite causes. But in the end, only one will win a coveted spot in the prestigious Drag Race Hall of Fame.
